HEADWORD: gumball
<hw>gum"ball`</hw> <pr>(g⟦ucr⟧m"b⟦add⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
piece of chewing gum in the shape of a ball, usually covered with a
colored glaze of sugar. They are often sold in a small, special-purpose
coin-operated vending machine called a <ecol><b>gumball
machine</b></ecol>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

